<h2>Utah Incentives & Rebates</h2>

<p>Utah offers several compelling financial incentives for solar and HVAC installations that significantly reduce upfront costs and improve return on investment. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the total cost of the solar system including equipment, installation, and associated electrical work, making it one of the most valuable incentives available.</p>

<p>The state of Utah provides additional support through its Renewable Energy Tax Credit, offering up to \$1,600 for residential solar installations. This state credit can be combined with the federal credit, providing substantial savings. Utah also offers a property tax exemption for renewable energy systems, meaning the added value of solar panels won't increase property tax assessments, providing ongoing savings for homeowners.</p>

<p>Rocky Mountain Power, Utah's primary utility company, operates a net metering program that credits customers for excess solar energy produced at the retail electricity rate. The utility also offers various energy efficiency rebates for HVAC systems, including up to \$700 for high-efficiency air conditioners, up to \$500 for ENERGY STAR heat pumps, and rebates for smart thermostats and duct sealing services. Additionally, Rocky Mountain Power's Wattsmart program provides rebates for whole-home energy efficiency upgrades when multiple improvements are made simultaneously.</p>

<p>Local utilities and municipalities throughout Utah often provide additional rebates and incentives. For example, Salt Lake City offers rebates for energy-efficient appliances and weatherization improvements, while Utah Associated Municipal Power Systems (UAMPS) member cities frequently provide their own solar and efficiency incentives. Many local programs also offer low-interest financing options for energy improvements, making upgrades more accessible to homeowners regardless of upfront capital availability.</p>

